<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0875 </DOCNO><TEXT>There will be rapid development in automated coal petrology and it isreasonable to expect that useful data could be developed by automatedmeans. This paper, completed on the basis of microscope photometry andimage analysis method, shows a reasonable technique and procedure forthe determination of maceral group composition and the reflectance ofvitrinite, which is introduced with optimum seeking method in 'fingerprint',and it also has such advantages as increased speed of analysis and reproducibilityof results.</TEXT></DOC>